                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-27T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. Our instruction no. 41 of February 16. Your telegram 62, April 10, noon.</p>
                <p>[Here follows summary of first paragraph of telegram from the President of the
                    Technical Board, Harbin, May 25, 8 a.m., printed <hi rend="italic"
                    >supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Confer with Foreign Office regarding situation. Point out that prompt decision as
                    to course of action is necessitated by these circumstances and find out whether
                    Japan is ready to offer any suggestions.</p>
                <p>Department assumes that message for Stevens in our 82 [<hi rend="italic"
                    >32</hi>], April 8, 6 p.m., was delivered to him. Please ask Stevens if he has
                    forwarded to us the report which that telegram called for stating his views with
                    regard to possibilities for the future and the policy which the United States
                    should pursue as to the Chinese Eastern Railway.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
